
Installing JX Memory Debugger:

The program (jx_memory_debugger) needs to be placed in a directory that is on your
execution path.  /usr/bin or ~/bin are usually good choices.


Running JX Memory Debugger:

If the program crashes or if you find other bugs, please check the web page
first to see if they have already been reported.


Notes on JX Memory Debugger:



The main Web page for JX Memory Debugger is

    http://newplanetsoftware.com/jx

